snippet: Jocelerme Privert, the country’s Senate leader, will lead a caretaker government to fill the void left by last week’s departure of President Michel Martelly.
abstract: Haiti's Senate leader Jocelerme Privert is elected provisional president of country in effort to fill vacuum left by departure of Pres Michel Martelly.
lead_paragraph: Jocelerme Privert, the country’s Senate leader, will lead a caretaker government to fill the void left by last week’s departure of President Michel Martelly.
